hopobject.body: A financial advisor purehealth.me Should Bill de Blasio slip below 40% in a final count of votes, we'd have the fourth runoff for mayor in the modern era ('73, '77, '01 and '13). Not likely, but certainly possible. And though he's coming under pressure from anxious fellow Democrats, Bill Thompson shouldn't withdraw. All the votes haven't been counted and I don't recall Hillary Clinton quitting in the spring of '08 for the sake of party unity once Barack Obama's nomination appeared inevitable.
